t: What Was Endless.com and Why Was it Discontinued?
s: March 18, 2021 - Endless.com was an e-commerce for shoes and accessories. Back then, Amazon owned two other fashion sites, making Endless.com obsolete in its portfolio.

September 12, 2024 - Endless.com was an American e-commerce site owned by Amazon, focused exclusively on shoes and accessories. Amazon closed Endless.com on September 27, 2012, and directed its customers to Amazon.com/Fashion. Endless.com was created in December 2007 by Amazon, as their first separate e-commerce brand.

t: Endless.com: Amazon Busts Out of Its Brand - Bloomberg
